}
```

Here's an example of a C procedure returning an integer:
```c
int reti()
{
     return 10;
}
```

A C procedure can return a floating-point value as follows:
```c
double retf()
{
     return 10.5;
}
```

Here's an example of a C procedure returning a character string:
```c
char *rets()
{
     return "Returned from rets";
}
```
The procedure must return a pointer to a valid address (a string constant or a static/global character buffer). It cannot return a pointer to a local character buffer.
